le to defy emasculation and adapt – at least temporarily – to their marginalized status as men.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aGender identityzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish menzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszGermanyxHistoryy1933-1945. 0aJewszGermanyxIdentityxHistoryy20th century. 0aMarginality, SocialzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aMasculinityzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aHolocaust.  aJewish men.  aJews.  aNazi Germany.  aThird Reich.  aWWII.  aWorld War Two.  aconcentration camps.  agender and war.  agender history.  agender identity.  agender.  amasculinity.  amen.  amilitary masculinity.  asocial history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishz978311099296008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022z9783110992939oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754125540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487541255423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487541255/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099296-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEG